news.headline: Wells Fargo spent years worried about the past. Now it can focus on the future.
news.summary: The fourth-largest US bank plans to pursue growth and expansion in investment banking, credit cards, and wealth management now that it has shed a major growth restriction imposed last decade by regulators as punishment for a fake accounts scandal.
